featured_reviews.review_id:
The historic Mecca Masjid is located adjacent to Charminar in a south-west direction. The construction of this mosque started in the year 1614 by Sultan Muhammad Qutb Shah and was Aurangzeb completed in 1693.

Muhammad Quli Qutb Shah established the city of Hyderabad in 1591, which would grow to encompass Golconda. He built the Charminar as the centerpiece of the city, as well as the Mecca Masjid, which is the largest mosque in the city with a capacity to accommodate 10,000 worshippers.

The Mecca Masjid, is the second largest Mosque in India and has witnessed some of the most critical moments in the history of Hyderabad. The Mecca Masjid, located at a distance of about 200 metres from the famous Charminar, is the second largest mosque in India.
